08/10/2004
SKOPJE, Macedonia -- A regional development conference opened in Skopje on Thursday (7 October), focusing on judicial reform. Macedonian Justice Minister Ixhet Memeti said that establishment of an independent and well-functioning judiciary is essential to eventual membership in the EU. The conference is being held under the auspices of the CARDS programme, an important part of the Stabilisation and Association Process. 
In other news, the OSCE mission in Skopje and the Council of Europe are holding a three-day training course for Macedonian lawyers. Experts are instructing 25 private, state and NGO lawyers on the European Convention on Human Rights as well as on procedures for filing complaints and appeals at the European Court of Human Rights. (MIA - 07/10/04) 
